reports that Iliya was sworn in on Oct. 3, being the most senior judge, following the mandatory retirement of Justice Hakeela Heman who served for over 20 years. Vanguard Nigeria News The Chief Justice of Nigeria, CJN, Justice Walter Onnoghen, on Saturday, swore-in Justice Abdu Kafarati as the Acting Chief Judge of the Federal High Court. September 16, 2017 In "News" Gov. Inuwa Yahaya, the newly sworn-in governor of Gombe State has suspended all appointments, contracts and allocations by the state and local government councils as from March 10. May 29, 2019 In "News" More details have emerged on why the Department of State Service, DSS, decided to clamp down on perceived corrupt judges across the federation, even as it deliberately sidelined the National Judicial Council, NJC, in the process. October 15, 2016 In "News"